file=Engineering/mia/operational/tool/mia-tool-requirements.md · h=name: mia-tool-requirements\ntype: operational/tool\nstatus: specifies needs, does not grant them — grants happen at deployment via config/connectors\nassigned_agent: mia (Engineering / Frontend Web)\ndate_added: 2026-07-09\n · p:=What mia needs, and what happens without each. Every external tool call is plan-locked (Rail 1) and sandboxed (Rail 2); mia runs no data changes (Rail 3).\n · tb=\| Need \| Tool / access \| Used by \| Without it \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| Repo read/write for frontend code \| repo scope (per stack-profile) \| all skills \| Core; without write, design-only \| · tb=\| Frontend framework + build \| per stack-profile \| all skills \| Method-only guidance \| · tb=\| Brand kit access \| atlas's kit (Brand Studio) \| design-tokens \| Provisional tokens, labeled; atlas is pending source of truth \| · tb=\| Token tooling \| Style Dictionary / CSS vars (per stack-profile) \| design-tokens \| Manual token management, labeled \| · tb=\| Agentation MCP \| agentation.com (proposed connector, §5) \| frontend-verification \| Feedback from description, labeled less precise \| · tb=\| Browser verification \| quinn's Reticle + Playwright \| frontend-verification \| Manual checklist; E-tier UNMET \| · tb=\| Perf tooling \| Lighthouse-class (per stack-profile) \| frontend-performance \| Emulated throttling, labeled fidelity gap \| · en(:Explicit non-needs (by design)=- **No data change execution** — mia builds UI; data changes are dana + operator (Rail 3).\n- **No production deploy control** — ops ships; mia's code passes quinn's gate first.\n- **No secrets in client code** — anything in the frontend bundle is public (aegis's concern).\n · n:=- mia is a primary builder with genuine code write access — every change passes dev's review (incl. integrity checks: mock data, hardcoded brand values), quinn's gate, and aegis for client-security surfaces.\n- Agentation + Reticle/Playwright are proposed connectors (plan §5), surfaced to the operator at deployment; skills degrade to method/manual without them.\n · tb=\| Tool \| Source \| Purpose \| Always-on \| · tb=\|------\|--------\|---------\|-----------\| · tb=\| **Browserbase MCP** \| [docs.browserbase.com/integrations/mcp](https://docs.browserbase.com/integrations/mcp) \| Cloud browser automation: cross-browser UI testing, visual regression via screenshots, mobile viewport verification. 6 tools: start, navigate, act, observe, extract, end. \| ⚠️ On-demand — activate during QA/verification phases \| · tb=\| **Website Cloner** \| [github.com/horuz-ai/claude-plugins](https://github.com/horuz-ai/claude-plugins) (website-cloner SKILL) \| 4-agent pipeline cloning sites into React+Tailwind: screenshotter → extractor → cloner → QA reviewer. Competitive design analysis, rapid prototyping from reference sites. \| ❌ No — expensive multi-agent pipeline; use /clone-website explicitly \| · tb=\| **awesome-design-md** \| [github.com/VoltAgent/awesome-design-md](https://github.com/VoltAgent/awesome-design-md) — MIT \| 70+ brand DESIGN.md files (Apple, Stripe, Linear, Vercel, Nike, etc.). Drop into project → AI agents generate brand-consistent UI. Bridges with Brand Studio/atlas design tokens. \| ⚠️ Reference — pull DESIGN.md when building UI, not a runtime tool \| · mmt:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=See Engineering/MCP-MARKETPLACE.md for setup instructions and full tool catalog.\n